---
import '../styles/global.css';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
// Symbiotic License Page
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		
		<title>The Symbiotic Licence - ResonantOS</title>
		<meta name="description" content="The Symbiotic Licence page now distinguishes the public licence text from the future DAO-issued Symbiotic Licence NFT credential." />
		
		<!-- Fonts -->
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
	</head>
	
	<body class="bg-black text-zinc-100 antialiased">
		<!-- Animated Background -->
		<div class="fixed inset-0 z-0">
			<div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-black via-zinc-950 to-black"></div>
			<div class="gradient-orb gradient-orb-1"></div>
			<div class="gradient-orb gradient-orb-2"></div>
		</div>

		<!-- Navigation -->
		<SiteNav />

		<!-- Content -->
		<main class="relative z-10 pt-24 pb-20">
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
				<!-- Header -->
				<div class="mb-16 text-center">
					<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light tracking-tight mb-6">
						The Symbiotic<br/>
						<span class="text-emerald-400">Licence</span>
					</h1>
					<p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 font-light">Legal text and DAO credential are being separated</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Content Card -->
				<div class="glass-card p-8 md:p-12 space-y-8">
					<!-- Preamble -->
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mb-4 text-emerald-400">Preamble</h2>
						<p class="text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
							The earlier page mixed two different things: a public licence for ResonantOS-related work, and the future Symbiotic Licence NFT. The current DAO design treats the NFT as an official, non-transferable credential that can only be issued to wallets with active Community membership.
						</p>
					</section>

					<!-- Section 1 -->
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mb-4 text-emerald-400">Section 1: Definitions</h2>
						<ul class="space-y-3 text-zinc-300">
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Public Licence Text:</strong> The human-readable legal or cultural agreement. Its canonical wording and hash must be finalized before mainnet.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Symbiotic Licence NFT:</strong> The DAO-issued credential that records licence and co-ownership status for a member wallet.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Community Member:</strong> A wallet with an active official Community Member record.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Credential Originality:</strong> A licence credential is original only if the official Membership Program recorded it.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Transferability:</strong> The credential is soulbound and cannot be sold or manually transferred.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<!-- Section 2 -->
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mb-4 text-emerald-400">Section 2: Credential Rules</h2>
						<p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">The on-chain licence credential should follow these rules:</p>
						<ul class="space-y-3 text-zinc-300 list-disc list-inside">
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Membership required:</strong> Only active Community Members can receive the Symbiotic Licence NFT.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">One per wallet:</strong> Duplicate licence credentials are rejected for the same active member record.</li>
							<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Non-transferable:</strong> Licence status stays with the wallet that received it.</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="text-zinc-300 mt-4">
							The licence NFT is a credential, not the full legal text. The canonical text and hash remain a mainnet requirement.
						</p>
					</section>

					<!-- Section 3 -->
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-2xl font-medium mb-4 text-emerald-400">Section 3: Current Implementation Status</h2>
						<p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">This page is intentionally not final legal text. The current implementation work is the DAO credential flow:</p>
						
						<div class="space-y-6">
							<div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-100 mb-2">Issue Flow</h3>
								<p class="text-zinc-300">
									The user reads the canonical licence text, signs its canonical hash, and the program verifies active Community Member status before issuing the licence credential.
								</p>
							</div>

							<div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-100 mb-2">DAO Record</h3>
								<p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">The Membership Program records the licence mint in the wallet's official MemberRecord.</p>
								
								<ul class="space-y-4 text-zinc-300">
									<li>
										<strong class="text-zinc-100">Originals are program-issued:</strong> Name, image, and metadata are not enough.
									</li>
									<li>
										<strong class="text-zinc-100">The record is the gate:</strong> Other contracts should verify the official record before granting licence-based rights.
									</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

							<div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-100 mb-2">Open Questions Before Mainnet</h3>
								<p class="text-zinc-300 mb-4">
									The DAO must finalize the canonical licence text, canonical hash, co-ownership scope, and any rights that depend on holding this credential.
								</p>
								<ul class="space-y-3 text-zinc-300 list-disc list-inside">
									<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Canonical hash:</strong> required for wallet signature verification.</li>
									<li><strong class="text-zinc-100">Rights model:</strong> required before public claims of co-ownership are final.</li>
								</ul>
							</div>

							<div>
								<h3 class="text-xl font-medium text-zinc-100 mb-2">Not a Transferable Asset</h3>
								<p class="text-zinc-300">
									The Symbiotic Licence NFT is not designed to be traded. It is a membership-based credential tied to the wallet that received it.
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</section>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>

		<style>
			.glass-card {
				background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
				backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
				border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
				border-radius: 1rem;
			}

			.gradient-orb {
				position: absolute;
				border-radius: 50%;
				filter: blur(80px);
				opacity: 0.3;
				animation: float 20s ease-in-out infinite;
			}

			.gradient-orb-1 {
				width: 500px;
				height: 500px;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #34d399 100%);
				top: -10%;
				left: -10%;
				animation-delay: 0s;
			}

			.gradient-orb-2 {
				width: 400px;
				height: 400px;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #d97706 0%, #b45309 100%);
				bottom: -10%;
				right: -10%;
				animation-delay: -10s;
			}

			@keyframes float {
				0%, 100% { transform: translate(0, 0) scale(1); }
				33% { transform: translate(30px, -30px) scale(1.1); }
				66% { transform: translate(-20px, 20px) scale(0.9); }
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>
